We're back again with the second half of the interview I did with Bob Walsh, author of the book MicroISV from vision to reality and founder of Safari Software.&nbsp;
http://www.safarisoftware.com 

In this episode Bob talks about how he's been a developer since 1983 and how after the dot com crash, finding himself working twice as hard for half as much he went into business for himself.
&nbsp;
Bob talks about the inspiration for his product, Master List Professional, why he chose windows and why he built a desktop application and finally closes with an look at the challenges of wearing so many hats as a MicroISV.
